{ Starting from the Old Benoni, white takes the pawn. }
1. dxc5 { And here comes the Gambit part... } 1... Na6 { Seen roughly 1% of the time, this is certainly a novelty. And while certainly not the top engine move(who cares about what the engine thinks anyway??), it is one way to regain the pawn. } 2. Be3 (2. b4? Nxb4) 2... Qa5+ (2... e6) *


