1. d5 { White pushes, gains center space, and refuses to trade a center pawn for a wing one. :( } 1... Nf6 { Key move of the Benoni-Indian. } 2. Nf3 { The next chapter is similar, but something I think should be noted is that from this move order, white is encouraged to take the pawn.
Source: me } *


